Emmanuel Bwacha, the Deputy Minority leader in the Senate, has joined the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC).  Bwacha, who represents Taraba South in the Senate, was formally received by President Buhari into the ruling APC at the State House on Thursday, February 3. Bwacha, in July 2018, mocked the APC, saying its leaders were secretly weeping over the mass defection of its members in the National Assembly. Bwacha was elected to the Senate to represent Taraba South Senatorial District of Taraba State in the 2011 general elections on the platform of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP). He was reelected under the same party in 2015 and won election again in 2019.  Source By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) The National Working Committee (NWC) of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) met on Thursday and nominated the senator representing Abia South, and former Deputy Governor of Abia State Enyinnaya Abaribe, as Minority Leader in the Ninth Senate. The NWC meeting was held in the… In "Top Stories" …As Senate receives report on 2021-2023 MTEF/FSP By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) -  Senators belonging to the Peoples’ Democratic Party on Wednesday commended President Buhari for his unique approach to governance. Two lawmakers who took their turns to speak on the floor during plenary, commended Buhari’s leadership style for… In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - South South senators have kicked as the National Working Committee (NWC) of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) plot to tinker with the list of selected principal officers of the party. There were unconfirmed reports on Tuesday that the NWC had concluded arrangements to… In "Top Stories"